article.headline: IUPUI 79, S. Dakota St. 57
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Robert Glenn scored 21 points to lead four IUPUI players in double figures Thursday night as the Jaguars defeated South Dakota State 79-57 in the Summit Conference opener for both teams. Leroy Nobles scored 16 points for IUPUI (6-2). Alex Young scored 13 and John Ashworth 10 for the Jaguars, who never trailed in the contest and led by as many as 30 points in the second half. Anthony Cordova scored 14 points to lead South Dakota State (2-5). Clint Sargent was the only other Jackrabbits player in double figures with 10. IUPUI, which led 43-28 at halftime, shot 55 percent from the field in the game. South Dakota State made 39 percent of its shots.
